\layout Subsection

I am only getting a few frames-per-second in xmame.x11/OpenGL.
 This sucks! What gives? 
\layout Itemize

You're probably running Mesa in software mode.
 You should read the "README.3Dfx" file in the Mesa distro.
 Specifically, you need to "setenv MESA_GLX_FX fullscreen".
\layout Itemize

You don't have a 3D graphics card.
 Go buy one (see below)!
\layout Subsection

When I run xmame.x11/OpenGL, it just dumps core.
 That's not as much fun as 3D Pac-Man, now is it?
\layout Itemize

If you are using a 3Dfx card, make sure you are running xmame.x11 as root.
 Root privileges are required to access the 3Dfx hardware.
\layout Itemize

If you're using Mesa and haven't upgraded to v3.0, do so.
 
\layout Subsection

When I run xmame.x11/OpenGL, everything is messed up.
\layout Standard

Read the above experiences, and try
